Comments (non-blocking):
1) The commit includes a large amount of generated build/cache artifacts (`frontend/.next/**`, `__pycache__/**`). These should not be versioned and create noisy, brittle diffs.
2) Backend keyword matching is English-substring based (`muscle`, `fat`, etc.), so non-English user text may often fall back to default (still localized). This meets language output requirements but reduces prompt-specific behavior in non-English conversations.

Security: none observed (no serious auth/injection/secrets regressions in changed source paths).

Next actions:
1) Remove generated artifacts from version control and add/verify ignore rules (`.next/`, `__pycache__/`).
2) Optionally extend keyword matching for non-English terms so localized quick prompts map to specific stub intents more reliably.
3) Add a lightweight integration test asserting language propagation and localized fallback/response behavior across the 6 supported languages.- âś… `frontend/app/api/chat/route.js`: reads `language` from request body and forwards as query param to backend.
