2) Backend keyword matching is English-substring based (`muscle`, `fat`, etc.), so non-English user text may often fall back to default (still localized). This meets language output requirements but reduces prompt-specific behavior in non-English conversations.

Security: none observed (no serious auth/injection/secrets regressions in changed source paths).

